<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These Rules are stipulated pursuant to Article 76 of the Cooperatives Act (hereinafter referred to as "the Act").
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Cooperatives shall be established within the scope wherein the members can perform cooperation.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Where the organizations of a cooperative are located in the administrative region of a municipality or county (city), the municipal or county (city) regulating authority shall be the regulating authority of the cooperative; where a cooperative spans two or more municipalities or counties (cities), the central regulating authority shall be the regulating authority of the cooperative.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[In order to increase the flexibility of business, the cooperatives may divide the members into several groups according to the category of the products or another standard, and each group may be solely engaged in one kind of business.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[According to the provision of Article 7 of the Act, cooperatives may apply to the regulating authority in charge of finance for exemption from income tax and business tax.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Where the establishment of a cooperative is approved according to the provision of Article 10 of the Act, the regulating authority shall issue an establishment registration certificate to the cooperative.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 7</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[A cooperative may prescribe in the constitution the number of shares that a member shall subscribe.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 8</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Upon buying shares of cooperatives, a member may pay the shares by the estimated value of properties other than currency according to the related provisions set forth in the constitution.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 9</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[To apply for registration of alteration due to reduction of the par value of each share or the guarantee money, a cooperative shall describe the result of announcement to the regulating authority and submit the resolution of the member's congress or the member representative's congress, the inventory of properties, and a statement of assets and liabilities.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 10</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[To call a meeting of the member's congress or the member representative's congress, the chairperson of the board of directors shall preside over the meeting; in absence of the chairperson of the board of directors, the meeting shall be presided over by the chairperson of the board of supervisors. If the chairperson of the board of supervisors is absent too, a person shall be temporarily elected to preside over the meeting.
When the board of directors calls a temporary meeting of the member's congress or the member representative's congress, the chairperson of the board of directors shall preside over the meeting; if the meeting is called by the supervisors or the members, a person shall be temporarily elected to preside over the meeting.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 11</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Where the chairperson of the board of directors or the board of supervisors doesn't call meetings according to the relevant provisions, an application signed by more than a half of all the directors or the supervisors may be submitted to the regulating authority, and the meeting may be called after the application is approved by the regulating authority. 
A meeting of the board of directors or the board of supervisors shall be presided over respectively by the chairperson of the board of directors or the board of supervisors; in absence of the chairperson, a person shall be temporarily elected to preside over the meeting.
A meeting called under Paragraph 1 shall be presided over by a person temporarily elected.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 12</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[In addition to the meetings set forth in the Act, cooperatives may hold various activities to invoke the consciousness of the members for gathering, and the main items may be prescribed in the constitution.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 13</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The regulating authority may send personnel to examine the accounting books of cooperatives as well as the documents set forth in Article 35 and Article 36, and may guide the fabrication and preparation of the documents where necessary.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 14</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Where a director, supervisor, or other personnel of a cooperative violates the provisions of the Act and these Rules, or doesn't deal with the affairs of the cooperatives according to the provisions of the constitution, thus resulting in damage to the cooperative or the members, the case shall be disposed according to law, and may be additionally disposed in the member's congress or representative's congress according to the provisions of the constitution.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 15</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The provisions set forth in these Rules on cooperatives shall also be applicable to cooperatives unions.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 16</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The format of the letters and forms set forth in the Act and these Rules shall be prescribed by the central regulating authority.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 17</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These Rules shall become effective as of the date of promulgation.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
</法規>
